    <briefdescription>
<para>Structure for storing date and time values with sub-second precision. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>The structure is 1-1 mapped to the struct tm for the members <computeroutput>tm_sec</computeroutput> to <computeroutput>tm_isdst</computeroutput> making it compatible with the standard time library.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="note"><para>Use <ref refid="group__rtc__interface_1gac2bb774a4b512f76c35a0a6723a7c807" kindref="member">rtc_time_to_tm()</ref> to safely cast from a <ref refid="structrtc__time" kindref="compound">rtc_time</ref> pointer to a <ref refid="structtm" kindref="compound">tm</ref> pointer. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
